% HTML Document Ontology - CNL Format
% Extends oo_ontology.cnl with HTML-specific concepts
%
% This ontology maps HTML-specific concepts to semantic analysis.
% All HTML entities use unified CNL names with language="html".
%
% Naming Convention:
%   - Concepts: hyphenated-lowercase (e.g., event-handler, form-input)
%   - Roles: hyphenated-lowercase forming natural sentences

% ============================================================================
% HTML-Specific Entity Types
% ============================================================================

% Document structure
Every html-document is a document.
Every html-element is an element.

% Scripts and styles
Every html-script is a script.
Every html-script-reference is a script-reference.
Every html-style-sheet is a style-sheet.

% Forms and inputs
Every html-form is a form.
Every html-form-input is a form-input.

% Links and resources
Every html-link is a link.
Every html-meta is a meta.
Every html-image is an image.
Every html-iframe is an iframe.

% Event handling
Every html-event-handler is an event-handler.

% ============================================================================
% Framework Directives
% ============================================================================

Every html-framework-indicator is a framework-indicator.
Every html-vue-directive is a vue-directive.
Every html-angular-directive is an angular-directive.
Every html-htmx-attribute is an htmx-attribute.
Every html-alpine-directive is an alpine-directive.
Every html-data-attribute is a data-attribute.

% Framework-specific subsumption
Every vue-directive is a framework-indicator.
Every angular-directive is a framework-indicator.
Every htmx-attribute is a framework-indicator.
Every alpine-directive is a framework-indicator.

% ============================================================================
% HTML Document Hierarchy
% ============================================================================

% Elements contained in documents
Every form is an element.
Every form-input is an element.
Every link is an element.
Every meta is an element.
Every image is an element.
Every iframe is an element.

% Scripts can be inline or external
Every inline-script is a script.
Every external-script is a script.

% ============================================================================
% HTML Patterns for Analysis
% ============================================================================

% Forms
Every form-with-action is a form.
Every form-with-method is a form.

% Security-related
Every script-without-integrity is a script.
Every form-without-csrf is a form.

% Framework detection patterns
Every vue-component is an element.
Every angular-component is an element.
Every htmx-enhanced-element is an element.
Every alpine-component is an element.
